digraph "real" {
  graph [label="Every type class that ℝ satisfies in Mathlib (leanprover-community/mathlib4 master, July 2026) — 214 of 417 satisfied classes shown.
An edge from S to T indicates that an instance of T can be derived from an instance of S.
Solid edges: `extends` parents / structure projections.  Dashed edges: derived `instance`s.  Bold amber outline: maximal — no other satisfied class implies it.
Transitively reduced (solid-preferring). Curation: most-referenced classes in core subject areas, closed under `extends`; details in the footer.", labelloc="t", fontsize=20, fontname="Helvetica,sans-Serif", rankdir=TB, ranksep=0.55, nodesep=0.18, compound=true];
  node [shape=box, style="rounded,filled", fontname="Helvetica,sans-Serif", fontsize=11, height=0.28, margin="0.08,0.03", color=black, penwidth=1];
